  "prompt": "When and how did Ambrose Bierce die?",
  "response": "Ambrose Bierce, the American writer and journalist, disappeared in late 1913 during a journey to Mexico. He was known for his sharp wit and dark humor, particularly in works like \"The Devil's Dictionary\" and his short stories. Despite various theories about his fate, including the possibility that he succumbed to old age or was involved in the Mexican Revolution, the exact details of his death remain unknown. He was last heard from in October 1913 when he wrote to a friend, mentioning his desire to join the fight against the Mexican government. His disappearance has led to much speculation, but no confirmed account of his death has been found.",
